1.  We'll start by creating our DEV environment folder from the command line: mkdir –p config/env/dev

2.  Next, we'll create our dev database con guration le in db.php under config/env/dev/. For now, we'll stick with a basic SQLite database:

     <?php return [
               'dsn' => 'sqlite:/' . __DIR__ .
               '/../../../runtime/db.sqlite', 

     'class' => 'yii\db\Connection',
               'charset' => 'utf8' 

    ];

3.  Next, we'll create our environment con guration le in env.php under config/env/dev. If you recall from earlier in the chapter, this is where our debug ag was stored, so this le will look as follows:

<?php return [
    'debug' => true 

];

Setting the web environment for NGINX

With our console application properly con gured, we now need to con gure our web server to pass the APPLICATION_ENV variable to our application. In a typical NGINX con guration, we have a location block that looks as follows:

 location ~ \.php$ {
           include fastcgi_params; 

 fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $document_root/
           $fastcgi_script_name;
           fastcgi_pass   127.0.0.1:9000;
           #fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php5-fpm.sock;
           try_files $uri =404; 

} To pass the APPLICATION_ENV variable to our application, all we need to do is de ne

a new fastcgi_param as follows: fastcgi_param APPLICATION_ENV "dev";

After making this change, simply restart NGINX.
